Most seen spieces¶

In [10]:
# creating search function
def most_seen_animal(df):
    # first benchamrk
    animal = df.iloc[0]
    name_animal_benchmark = animal.scientific_name
    observations_benchmark = animal.observations 
    #comparing with benchmark
    for i in range(len(df)):
        animal = df.iloc[i]
        name_animal = animal.scientific_name
        observations = animal.observations
        if observations > observations_benchmark:
            name_animal_benchmark= name_animal
            observations_benchmark = observations
    
    #finding common_name
    for x in range(len(spec)):
        animal_spec = spec.iloc[x]
        scientific_name = animal_spec.scientific_name
        if scientific_name == name_animal_benchmark:
            name_animal_benchmark = animal_spec.common_names
            category = animal_spec.category
            break
    
    #returning values
    return name_animal_benchmark, observations_benchmark, category

def groupby_category(df):
#finding categories
    df= df.merge(spec, on= "scientific_name", how="inner")
#grouping by it
    group = df.groupby("category").observations.sum().reset_index()
    total_observ = observ.observations.sum()
    #group = group.observations.apply(lambda x: x)
    return group

In [20]:
#creating list
unique_scientific_name= list(observ_common_name.scientific_name.unique())
best_park = []
scientific_name = []
common_names = []
category = []

for name in unique_scientific_name:
    #creating df
    spieces_df = observ_common_name[observ_common_name.scientific_name == name]
    observations_list= list(spieces_df.observations)

    #finding the best
    index= 5
    benchmark = 0
    for i in range(len(observations_list)):
        observations= observations_list[i]
        if observations > benchmark:
            benchmark = observations
            index = i

    #selecting the best
    best_park.append(spieces_df.iloc[index].park_name)
    scientific_name.append(name)
    
    #adding extra informations
    common_names.append(spieces_df.common_names.iloc[0])
    category.append(spieces_df.category.iloc[0])
